title: Grateful Dead Live at Providence Civic Center on 1985-04-04
lineage: XLII tapes BX-300 w/o Dolby on playback > Philips standalone CDR > CDWav to split and encode as Flac (level 5).
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Jack Straw, Dire Wolf, El Paso, She Belongs To Me, My Brother Esau, Friend Of The Devil, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Deal

Set 2

I Need A Miracle-> Crazy Fingers, Samson & Delilah, He's Gone-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Black Peter-> Around & Around-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: A better copy is needed of this and other Providence, RI shows from 84-87` I went to them all as a child when I was in high school, were my say 4th - 50th shows, and I have sought to hear them all, and know they need upgrades. This is pretty ok and the show was GREAT, but this sounds like the recording that's been circulating since 4 2 85, or, forever since I first went to the show and got the....TAPE.. If anyone has upgrades please do and consider the other shows in this venue. there all good but 84-87/88 Providence has had no 5 star recordings and no one seems to know how good these shows are, for example the Playin-China Doll High time on 4 27 84. That's the stuff I'd pay 150 to see.......again. and will on 7/18/17 w/o Jerry.

your rain falls like crazy fingers I just love this show!
Very creative first set and super cool pre-drums.
